This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with spoken dialog systems and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves machine learning techniques such as LSTM networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training models. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with dialog systems.
